Interface EnhancedIterable<A>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the element type
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<A>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FiniteIterable<A>, ImmutableFiniteIterable<A>, ImmutableIterable<A>, ImmutableNonEmptyFiniteIterable<A>, ImmutableNonEmptyIterable<A>, ImmutableNonEmptySet<A>, ImmutableNonEmptyVector<A>, ImmutableSet<A>, ImmutableVector<A>, NonEmptyFiniteIterable<A>, NonEmptyIterable<A>, NonEmptySet<A>, NonEmptyVector<A>, Set<A>, Vector<A>

    public interface EnhancedIterable<A>
extends java.lang.Iterable<A>
    An Iterable with some additional methods.

    May be infinite, finite, or empty.

    Any Iterable can be upgraded to an EnhancedIterable by calling enhancedIterable(Iterable)}.

        default EnhancedIterable<A> drop(int count)
        Returns a new EnhancedIterable that drops the first count elements of this EnhancedIterable.
        Parameters:
        count - the number of elements to drop from this EnhancedIterable. Must be >= 0. May exceed size of this EnhancedIterable, in which case, the result will be an empty EnhancedIterable.
        Returns:
        an EnhancedIterable<A>
